	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I've decided to post some clarification on this quest, mainly because I've used this page for many other quests, but the info on this one is surprisingly lacking, and because I finally completed it tonight.<BR>
<BR>
First, you have to talk to the Wizard on the second level of the Crimson Hand tower in the palace about his [special matter].  If you don't talk to him, the skeleton you are looking for will not be spawned...I found that out after days of searching.<BR>
Once you've done that, go out to the Toxx and look for the only skeleton that judges you amiably when you consider him, that's the only difference between him and the other skeletons.  You should find him South of the first kobold camp, but be prepared to look for days of game time.<BR>
After you have finally found him, ask him &quot;Where is the scroll?&quot;, hailing him will do nothing.  He will answer &quot;Kobold, kobold.&quot;, and will lead you to where the kobold caster will spawn.  Yes, it is a caster, not a shaman, and it's about level 7.  I managed to kill it at level 8, but it took all my mana, so I had to finish it off with my staff, being heavily buffed at the time.  I think it has a high magic resistance, because all my spells did about half of what they normally do.<BR>
If you manage kill him, you get half a spell scroll off his corpse, which you take back to the Wizard, and he will give you the completed Column of Frost spell, faction, and experience.<BR>
<BR>
Yes, it is a long and mostly boring quest...most of the time just searching the Toxx for this skeleton, but it is worth it, just to save the 4+ pp it would take to buy the spell.  And as my good friend Alidaar said as we were doing this quest, hunting one specific prey is a great challange.  Best of luck to all my fellow Wizards.<BR>
<BR>
Morf.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
